152
00:09:52.049 --> 00:09:55.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nobu’s at work right now
and said he may be a bit late.

153
00:09:57.013 --> 00:09:59.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shin, you should return home
once in a while.

154
00:10:00.433 --> 00:10:02.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll bet your parents are worried.

155
00:10:03.561 --> 00:10:04.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They’re not.

156
00:10:04.937 --> 00:10:07.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really? Then it’s fine, I guess.

157
00:10:12.236 --> 00:10:14.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re different, Nana.

158
00:10:14.405 --> 00:10:15.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Usually, everyone says,

159
00:10:15.448 --> 00:10:18.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"You’re mistaken.
Of course they’re worried."

160
00:10:19.869 --> 00:10:24.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it’s a fact that there are parents
who abandon their children.

161
00:10:29.754 --> 00:10:31.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A junior high student?

162
00:10:31.213 --> 00:10:34.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That guy who came by the store
about the bassist ad, right?

163
00:10:34.383 --> 00:10:35.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Didn’t he say he was eighteen?

164
00:10:36.052 --> 00:10:37.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Actually, he’s fifteen.

165
00:10:38.471 --> 00:10:40.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nana cornered him with a few questions,
and he confessed.

166
00:10:40.139 --> 00:10:42.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He told us he thought
they wouldn’t take him seriously

167
00:10:42.141 --> 00:10:44.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if he said he was a junior high student.

168
00:10:44.143 --> 00:10:46.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, but it’s April,
so maybe he’s in tenth grade now.

169
00:10:47.063 --> 00:10:48.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Although he doesn’t seem
to be going to high school.

170
00:10:48.731 --> 00:10:51.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh? Maybe he didn’t bother
taking the entrance exams.

171
00:10:51.192 --> 00:10:54.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm… I really don’t know.

172
00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:56.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He doesn’t go into detail
about such things.

173
00:10:57.073 --> 00:10:58.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There seems to be more to it
under the surface.

174
00:10:58.991 --> 00:11:00.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm.

175
00:11:00.826 --> 00:11:05.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Anyway, he doesn’t go home much,
so I’m somewhat concerned.

176
00:11:05.831 --> 00:11:08.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m sure his parents are totally worried.

177
00:11:09.627 --> 00:11:11.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I guess so.

178
00:11:11.128 --> 00:11:13.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And we still haven’t found a drummer.

179
00:11:13.381 --> 00:11:15.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s like our luck’s running out.

180
00:11:15.591 --> 00:11:18.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But didn’t you say there was
a guy who tried out?

181
00:11:18.511 --> 00:11:20.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nana turned him down,
saying she didn’t like him.

182
00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:23.933 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Although the others said
he was pretty good.

183
00:11:25.518 --> 00:11:27.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really? She must have high standards.

184
00:11:27.770 --> 00:11:31.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or rather, I think she’s in love with Yasu

185
00:11:31.774 --> 00:11:33.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and therefore refuses to accept
a different drummer.

186
00:11:33.651 --> 00:11:35.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who is Yasu?

187
00:11:35.236 --> 00:11:37.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He was her band’s leader back
in her hometown.

188
00:11:37.238 --> 00:11:39.657 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He’s a skinhead,
and he and Nana look so cute together.

189
00:11:40.825 --> 00:11:42.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can just imagine.

190
00:11:42.535 --> 00:11:45.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, Mr. Mizukoshi, is it okay
if I order the meat and potato dish, too?

191
00:11:45.871 --> 00:11:47.164 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go ahead.

192
00:11:49.125 --> 00:11:50.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m so full!

193
00:11:51.001 --> 00:11:52.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is happiness!

194
00:11:53.629 --> 00:11:56.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That’s great. But was the tavern
really okay for you?

195
00:11:57.049 --> 00:11:59.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yup! I love taverns.

196
00:11:59.510 --> 00:12:00.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you for the meal.

197
00:12:01.846 --> 00:12:02.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nana!

198
00:12:05.141 --> 00:12:06.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you all right?

199
00:12:07.268 --> 00:12:08.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think I might’ve had
a little too much to drink.

200
00:12:08.936 --> 00:12:10.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How embarrassing.

201
00:12:16.861 --> 00:12:17.987 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Oops!</i>

202
00:12:19.155 --> 00:12:21.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Well, I should be going now.
-Wait, Nana!

203
00:12:25.744 --> 00:12:28.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To be honest, I asked you out today

204
00:12:28.122 --> 00:12:30.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because I wanted to talk to you
about something important.

205
00:12:30.249 --> 00:12:32.835 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Huh? Wait a minute.</i>

206
00:12:33.502 --> 00:12:36.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ve been waiting for the right time,

207
00:12:36.881 --> 00:12:38.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I just couldn’t bring myself
to tell you.

208
00:12:39.008 --> 00:12:42.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This could come as a surprise to you.

209
00:12:43.262 --> 00:12:45.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
