00:13:30.476 --> 00:13:31.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Mr. Mizukoshi…</i>

221
00:13:33.521 --> 00:13:36.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You see, I plan on closing the shop.

222
00:13:41.862 --> 00:13:44.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m sorry. Business isn’t going well.

223
00:13:50.496 --> 00:13:53.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is real trouble!

224
00:14:05.135 --> 00:14:07.012 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh! My shoe!

225
00:14:08.180 --> 00:14:09.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Shoji!
-Huh?

226
00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:13.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry, Shoji. Go on ahead.
You’ll miss the last train!

227
00:14:13.227 --> 00:14:14.311 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey!

228
00:14:39.044 --> 00:14:41.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You knew you would have to run
for the last train,

229
00:14:41.589 --> 00:14:44.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so why did you wear those shoes?

230
00:14:58.314 --> 00:14:59.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I did it on purpose.

231
00:15:09.909 --> 00:15:11.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
NANA

232
00:15:18.208 --> 00:15:19.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello?

233
00:15:19.293 --> 00:15:21.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shoji!

234
00:15:21.795 --> 00:15:24.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Help me!

235
00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:37.937 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is for the taxi.

236
00:15:38.562 --> 00:15:41.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's all right.
It’s on my way home anyway.

237
00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:44.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it was my fault
we missed the last train.

238
00:15:44.276 --> 00:15:45.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It really is okay.

239
00:15:52.701 --> 00:15:56.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shoji, that call earlier…
It was from your girlfriend, right?

240
00:16:02.920 --> 00:16:06.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s my policy not to accept money
from a guy who has a girlfriend.

241
00:16:15.599 --> 00:16:16.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good night.

242
00:16:36.245 --> 00:16:40.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It appears that this is
all the money I have right now.

243
00:16:41.083 --> 00:16:44.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why? You’re always working so hard.

244
00:16:44.670 --> 00:16:46.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You really are spending it all on Sachiko!

245
00:16:46.797 --> 00:16:49.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re wrong! In fact, I bought that!

246
00:16:53.053 --> 00:16:54.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A computer. And it’s a Mac.

247
00:16:55.055 --> 00:16:59.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nice, isn’t it? I’m studying
computer graphic design, after all.

248
00:16:59.518 --> 00:17:00.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wonder if we can get
a good price for it.

249
00:17:00.519 --> 00:17:01.353 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Cut it out!

250
00:17:01.437 --> 00:17:04.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But how else am I gonna get
proper food starting tomorrow?

251
00:17:04.815 --> 00:17:07.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right! I’ll share this with you.

252
00:17:07.109 --> 00:17:09.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pickled plums made by my grandma.

253
00:17:10.195 --> 00:17:14.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shoji, you idiot! You’re of no use!

254
00:17:17.703 --> 00:17:20.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>So, now that I was unemployed, I was lost,</i>

255
00:17:20.622 --> 00:17:25.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>seriously contemplating the possibility</i>
<i>of starving to death on the streets.</i>

256
00:17:26.253 --> 00:17:28.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Thank you for choosing Shuei Bank…</i>

257
00:17:28.464 --> 00:17:29.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
300,000 yen?

258
00:17:29.882 --> 00:17:30.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s right!

259
00:17:30.799 --> 00:17:34.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Mizukoshi deposited
300,000 yen in severance pay!

260
00:17:34.178 --> 00:17:36.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you sure you that’s not 30,000?

261
00:17:36.638 --> 00:17:39.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your remaining salary would’ve
amounted to around that much.

262
00:17:39.266 --> 00:17:41.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
