274
00:18:02.372 --> 00:18:05.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Natsuko Komatsu. That’s my mom!

275
00:18:05.209 --> 00:18:06.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re a long way from independence

276
00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:08.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if you’re crying to your parents
for money.

277
00:18:08.712 --> 00:18:12.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Huh? But I didn’t tell her
I was having money problems!

278
00:18:12.883 --> 00:18:15.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought if I told them,
they would make me go back home.

279
00:18:18.305 --> 00:18:20.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How did she know?

280
00:18:20.808 --> 00:18:22.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Could it be maternal instinct?

281
00:18:29.983 --> 00:18:30.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, right.

282
00:18:30.901 --> 00:18:34.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, Nana. Now that I have all this money,
let’s celebrate with sukiyaki tonight.

283
00:18:34.988 --> 00:18:35.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

284
00:18:36.073 --> 00:18:37.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Back home, my mom would make sukiyaki

285
00:18:37.866 --> 00:18:39.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when we had something to celebrate.

286
00:18:39.451 --> 00:18:41.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let’s go back to the supermarket
to buy what we need.

287
00:18:41.203 --> 00:18:42.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You…

288
00:18:42.121 --> 00:18:44.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
